Package: eiCalibrate
Title: Empirical Bayes Calibration for Ecological Inference
Version: 0.3.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Loren", "Collingwood", email = "lcollingwood@unm.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Tools for jointly tuning both Dirichlet concentration parameters
    (lambda1, lambda2) in RxC ecological inference (as implemented in
    'eiPack::ei.MD.bayes') against known benchmarks from a calibration
    election, then applying the calibrated priors to a target election.
    Supports both 1D (tied lambda1=lambda2) and 2D (independent) calibration
    grids with optional replication averaging to smooth MCMC noise. Includes
    unified wrappers for 'eiPack' RxC, 'eiCompare' iterative 2x2, and
    Goodman's ecological regression, plus sensitivity-sweep and multi-method
    comparison utilities. Intended for Voting Rights Act-style racially
    polarized voting analysis where the standard prior may over-shrink
    estimates toward the pooled mean under low-data conditions.
